    <item>
      <title>How to setup InfluxDB, Chronograf and Telegraf for development</title>
      <link>https://petar-slat.from.hr/post/2016/04/how-to-setup-influxdb-chronograf-and-telegraf-for-development/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Apr 2016 13:29:56 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://petar-slat.from.hr/post/2016/04/how-to-setup-influxdb-chronograf-and-telegraf-for-development/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;InfluxDB, Chronograf and Telegraf are part of TICK stack from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.influxdata.com/time-series-platform/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;InfluxData&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To install it on Ubuntu you could use apt-get package manager, or install it via .deb package. I prefer the second method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find install instructions on their &lt;a href=&#34;https://influxdata.com/downloads/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;download&lt;/a&gt; page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After installation there are two config files you have to change a little to make things work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First one is located in /opt/chronograf/ under name âconfig.tomlâ. Inside you have to expose Chronograf to public internet (see picture).&lt;/p&gt;
















&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-chronograf-config&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Chronograf config&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /post/2016/04/how-to-setup-influxdb-chronograf-and-telegraf-for-development/ChronografConfig_hu0c938e63f0f830080e76675c01932eb7_111813_1d93799d9efc224b85f6db966c3bf543.webp 400w,
               /post/2016/04/how-to-setup-influxdb-chronograf-and-telegraf-for-development/ChronografConfig_hu0c938e63f0f830080e76675c01932eb7_111813_d313192b46c09071a0f6e607b8c9ac9a.webp 760w,
